Docs.summary: Returns the maximum length of byte array that can be used to specify a Aware service specific information field: the arbitrary load used in discovery or the message length of Aware message exchange.

remarks.para: Returns the maximum length of byte array that can be used to specify a Aware service specific information field: the arbitrary load used in discovery or the message length of Aware message exchange. Docs.summary: Returns the set of cipher suites supported by the device for use in Wi-Fi Aware data-paths.
Docs.value: A set of flags from #WIFI_AWARE_CIPHER_SUITE_NCS_SK_128, #WIFI_AWARE_CIPHER_SUITE_NCS_SK_256, #WIFI_AWARE_CIPHER_SUITE_NCS_PK_128, or #WIFI_AWARE_CIPHER_SUITE_NCS_PK_256

remarks.para: Returns the set of cipher suites supported by the device for use in Wi-Fi Aware data-paths. The device automatically picks the strongest cipher suite when initiating a data-path setup.
